  <title translate="true">XS1721</title>
  <body>
    <header>
      <para styleclass="Heading1"><text styleclass="Heading1" translate="true">XS1721</text></para>
    </header>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">Class &apos;class&apos; cannot have multiple base classes: &apos;class_1&apos; and &apos;class_2&apos;</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">The most common cause of this error message is attempting to use multiple inheritance. A class in C# may only inherit directly from one class. However, a class can implement any number of interfaces.</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"></para>
    <para styleclass="Heading2"><text styleclass="Heading2" translate="true">Example</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">The following example shows one way in which SC1721 is generated, and then shows two possible ways to avoid the error.</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"></para>
    <para styleclass="Code with box"><text styleclass="Code with box" translate="true">// CS1721.cs &#160;</text><br/><text styleclass="Code with box" translate="true">public class A {} &#160;</text><br/><text styleclass="Code with box" translate="true">public class B {} &#160;</text><br/><text styleclass="Code with box" translate="true">public class MyClass : A, B {} &#160; // CS1721 &#160;</text><br/><br/><text styleclass="Code with box" translate="true">// One possible fix is to use the following approach instead: &#160;</text><br/><text styleclass="Code with box" translate="true">public class A {} &#160;</text><br/><text styleclass="Code with box" translate="true">public class B : A {} &#160;</text><br/><text styleclass="Code with box" translate="true">public class C : B {} &#160;</text><br/><br/><text styleclass="Code with box" translate="true">// Another possible fix is to use interfaces instead of base classes: &#160;</text><br/><text styleclass="Code with box" translate="true">public class A {} &#160;</text><br/><text styleclass="Code with box" translate="true">public interface B {} &#160;</text><br/><text styleclass="Code with box" translate="true">public class C : A, B {} &#160;</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> &#160;</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"></para>
  </body>
</topic>
